<div style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); padding: .1em 1em;
            border-radius: 1em; margin-top: 25px; font-size: .9em;">
  <p>
    My name is Avand and I’m building While because I love outlines and I love
    todo lists. In high school, I typed up the most incredible outlined notes. I
    also love making lists and crossing off todos. I’ve tried out almost every
    todo list app out there but couldn’t find anything that worked quite like I
    wanted. So, since I design and build web apps for a living, I decided to
    build While to “scratch my own itch.”
  </p>

  <p>
    For me, grouping todos is just as important as the todo itself. So I decided
    to give them a 50/50 split in importance within While. A todo is, of course,
    a “check-off-able” task. But it’s also a folder for other todos. One task
    can very easily be broken into smaller ones. And you can jump around quickly
    and move stuff around as you’d expect.
  <p>

  <p>
    I designed While to be fun, fast, and free.
  </p>

  <p>
    I love todo lists and this is my favorite one.
  </p>

  <p>
    I hope you enjoy it,<br>
    — Avand
  </p>
